title: For Sale:  RCBS Reloading Dies - 7mm WSM
postcontent:
This two-die set is intended for reloading bottleneck cases, and consists of a Full-Length Sizer Die with an Expander-Decapping Unit, and a Seater Die with Bullet Seater Plug. The Full-Length Sizer Die brings the case to SAAMI minimum cartridge dimensions. It sizes the outside of the case, de-primes and expands the neck to accept the bullet. The die has vents to prevent case damage caused by trapped air and for excessive lubricant. Headspace is held to minimum tolerances to avoid changing the case body length during full length sizing. The included Seater Die has a built-in roll crimper to secure the bullet at the same time as it's seated.

Feel free to give me a call at REDACTED with any questions.

title: For Sale:  1944 Finnish M39 with US arsenal marked Westinghouse bolt, antique reciever
postcontent:
1944 VKT M39, SA and D marked barrel shank, antique 1896 Tula receiver, postwar arctic birch stock (late style splice, butt reinforcements), stock still has pine tar! Bluing is typical for age (fair to poor, no rust etc). Bore is good, gun is accurate.  test fired for accuracy, then cleaned and stored.  5-digit Finnish serial number

Highly unusual bolt, including markings from all 3 New England Westinghouse facilities (Meridian, Chicopee Falls, and East Springfield) plus the US arsenal flaming bomb. This was a US manufactured bolt that was purchased by the US when Russia defaulted on the Westinghouse contract, and likely was issued to US troops during the 1918 Siberian expedition.  It evidently made its way to Finland at some point thereafter, then back to the states almost 100 years later. Quite a trip.
Magazine follower is also marked with the Westinghouse logo.

As a 1896 receiver, gun is classified as an antique by the ATF, and is therefore legal for interstate sales without a background check.  I will consider buyers from neighboring states, but will ask to see ID.  All state, federal, and local laws apply as with any private sale :)
